scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series contains pamphlets, correspondence, memorandums, brochures, newsletters, application packets, proposal, by-laws, press releases, posters, and handbooks. They range in date from 1913 to 2004. The materials concern the style for George Washington University's theses and dissertations for master's students; courses; requirements; deans; admission information; the Radiological Sciences program; faculty by-laws; fellowships; scholarships; graduate assistantships; enrollment; "The Virtual Trail: political journalism on the Internet"; the Institute for Politics, Democracy & the Internet; the Graduate School of Political Management; degree programs; off-campus programs; student handbooks; a Graduate Student in Genetics handbook; the School of Media and Public Affairs's Journalism Department; the Political Science Department; the Sociology Department; the Robert A. Taft Institute of Government Seminars; awards and prizes; and the Columbian College of Arts and Science.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series contains annual reports and Ph.D. statistics from 1907-1967, and "daily life files" from 1972-1977. The daily life files are chronolgoical files of memoranda and correspondence produced by the office of Henry Solomon, dean of the Graduate School of Arts and Sciences, except for the daily life files labled "Manpower." These are chronological files of correspondence and reports related to the Econometric Research on Navy Manpower Problems program.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series contains minutes of the Graduate Council, dissertation lists, and course brochures, in addition to a paper on Bearcreek, Montana coal mining. They range in date from 1939-57.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series contains dean's departmental files for American Studies, Art Therapy, Chemistry, Biochemistry, Center for Washington Area Studies, Corcoran Hall renovation, Classics, History, German, Women's Studies, School of Education, School of Medicine, School of Engineering, School of Government, International Student Services, and prizes and awards. They range in date from 1943-88.
